I have another use case for storing and using the latest version of a data source for providers:

Suppose I have the following sample program (see end), which creates a CRD (in my demo only the actual secret, but I have the initial case of a CRD) with the Kubernetes provider. The CRD controller then creates a secret in the background when processing the CRD. If this secret contains data that a provider should use, the secret data source of the Kubernetes provider can be helpful. After successful import, the provider can be configured and used (in this case also the Kubernetes provider for illustrative purposes).

This will also work for the first application. For any further apply where something changes in the CRD (in my case I just added a label to the secret in the kubernetes_manifest resource), this no longer works because the data source can now only be read at runtime (see Dependencies). The provider will use the default values (in case of the kubernetes provider its "localhost:443") and tries to manage the resources wouldnt help you

Simple example code:

```hcl
